    "Q12. For a normal distribution data what is the relationship between its measure of central tendency?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fd624685-bbf4-4d43-9f00-c3fd9b03ddb6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Mean (μ): The mean is the average of all data points. In a normal distribution, it is located at the center of the distribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "Median (Mdn): The median is the middle value of a dataset when it is ordered in ascending or descending order. For a normal distribution, the mean and median are the same, as the data is symmetrically distributed around the center.\n",
    "\n",
    "Mode (Mo): The mode is the value that occurs most frequently in a dataset. In a normal distribution, the highest point on the probability density function is the mode, and it is also equal to the mean and median."
   ]
  },
